Path B — End-to-End Summary
Path B rebuilt RESTest into MIST: cleanly separated the entry point, the test-case generator, and the new oracle/fault-taxonomy work into a 4-module Maven reactor, and added the production wiring those modules were missing.

Phase 1 — Decouple MIST from RESTest (d163359e)
Introduced a MIST-owned entry point (MistMain / MistRunner) so the orchestrator no longer lives in the RESTest namespace.
Why: the project shipped under the legacy RESTest brand even though every code path was MIST-shaped. Example: a user running java -jar restest.jar … had no way to tell which tool they were actually invoking.

Phase 2 — Trace Shape Oracle scaffolding (2a822611, b017530a deleted the legacy SoftErrorRuleCache)
Added mist-core/io.mist.core.oracle.shape.*: TraceShapeOracle, TraceShapeLearner, ShapeInvariantStore, and four invariants (SpanTreeShapeInvariant, StatusPropagationInvariant, TimingEnvelopeInvariant, ResponseEnvelopeInvariant).
Why: faults were judged purely by HTTP response shape. Example: a 200 OK whose downstream tree silently skipped the payment service used to slip through — now SPAN_TREE_SHAPE flags the missing edge.

Phase 3 — Adaptive Fault Taxonomy scaffolding (d6ac2b87, cd45aa41 retired the InvalidInputType enum)
Replaced the hard-coded enum with FaultTypeRegistry + ApplicabilityMatrix, all keyed by MistInvalidInputPool.
Why: InvalidInputType was a closed enum — adding a new fault required code change + recompile. Example: a domain-specific STALE_JWT fault is now a registry entry, not a Java edit.

Stage 1.C — Split into reactor (ea60d114)
Broke the monolith into mist-parent / mist-core / mist-llm / mist-restest-adapter / mist-cli.
Why: mist-cli previously pulled in the entire RESTest writer just to load an OpenAPI spec. Now the CLI depends only on mist-core.

Stage 1.D — Byte-identical gate (5889149f, 2151c9e7)
Made MistMain produce byte-for-byte identical generator output to the legacy entry point; pinned snakeyaml; seeded the LLM-fallback placeholder.
Why: if the new entry point silently changed even one byte of the generated test code, we couldn't claim a clean migration.

Usability fixes (fe207b5e, 93ed4337, 3d878f6d)
INPUT paths now resolve relative to the .properties file; MistRunner's test-class lookup honours inputs.targetDirJava; IntelliJ run configs are checked in.
Why: example — inputs.openAPISpec=api.yaml used to resolve against the JVM CWD (random, depending on how you launched), so it broke whenever you ran from anywhere other than the repo root.

CLI tool replacement (8d82bffb)
MicroserviceConfBuilderMain (RESTest-flavoured) replaced by io.mist.cli.MistConfGenMain.

Docs + scrub (a3694b6e, 714d09c5, fe0a66d7, 583908b9)
README rewritten MIST-first; user-visible "RESTest-core" wording scrubbed; seed-trace-labels.json explained.

Follow-up round — production wiring (three sibling branches off 714d09c5)

c916ddfd — moved the LLM SPI (LLMClient, LLMCallCache) into the now-empty mist-llm module so the CLI can call LLMs without dragging in the RESTest writer.
1744d735 — replaced the hard-coded 3-entry FaultMiner stub with a real LLM-driven miner that reads FaultDetectionTracker history, prompts the configured client, and caches by SHA-256 for reproducibility.
0711a4f6 — wired TraceShapeOracle into MistRunner + MultiServiceRESTAssuredWriter (Allure verdict attachment, negative-variant FAIL→PASS on RESPONSE_ENVELOPE, positive-variant fail on any ERROR violation). Bridged Jaeger JSON via the new TraceShapeAdapter.
